Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Chop the @New Potatoes{1} in half (or quarters if they're very big!). Pop them on a #baking tray{} and drizzle over @oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{} and put them on the top shelf of your oven to cook for ~{30%minutes} or until they are crispy and brown.

Peel and finely chop the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and chop the @Olives{3}(chopped up into very small pieces) up into very small pieces (¼cm if you can manage it!). Finely chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{3}(finely chopped).

Mix your chopped parsley with your chopped olives, garlic, @Lemon{1/2}(juiced) and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Whisk it together thoroughly and leave to the side.

> A fork works well for this!

Bring a #pot{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cut the very top and bottoms from the @Green Beans{1}. Add them to the boiling water and cook for ~{3%mins}, then drain and run cold water through them to stop them cooking anymore.

> This is called 'top and tailing!'.

About 6 mins before the potatoes are cooked, add @oil{1%tbsp} to a #frying pan{} on medium heat. Season the @Sea Bass Fillets{2} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @black pepper{}, once the pan is hot add the sea bass skin-side down. Cook for ~{3%mins} on one side before turning over to cook for ~{2%mins} on the other side. Then remove the sea bass from the pan to the plates you will serve them on and squeeze @Lemon{1%tbsp}(juiced) over each fillet.

Add your drained green beans to the frying pan (no need to wash!) and stir-fry for a couple of mins before serving on the plates with your sea bass crispy potatoes, and your salsa verde on top ... enjoy!